DLW-SPUN · the full weave of No Heroes Here

who   : No Heroes Here — No Heroes Here (the thesis of the cycle).
what  : The Gap Cycle keeps no heroes. It keeps a dragon's greed, a god who pays, a monster who reaches for grace, a survivor who chooses anyway — and asks whether the will to choose, freely, is the only freedom there is. The Ring reforged: power corrupts, transformation costs the self, and redemption is possible only at a price no hero would pay. That is the parable. Witness it.
where : No Heroes Here · the thesis of the cycle, within The Gap Cycle.
why   : to hold the office this roll assigns: the thesis of the cycle.
when  : across the events of The Gap Cycle (as the lineage records).
how   : The Gap Cycle keeps no heroes. It keeps a dragon's greed, a god who pays, a monster who reaches for grace, a survivor who chooses anyway — and asks whether the will to choose, freely, is the only freedom there is. The Ring reforged: power corrupts, transformation costs the self, and redemption is possible only at a price no hero would pay. That is the parable. Witness it.

